---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import CTA from '../components/CTA.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Download"
  description="Install Perspectiv on a Linux host in about 10 minutes. Docker Compose bundle, free 30-day trial, no credit card required."
>
  <section class="bg-gradient-to-b from-slate-50 to-white py-20 sm:py-24">
    <div class="container-prose text-center">
      <p class="section-eyebrow">Download Perspectiv</p>
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight text-slate-900 sm:text-5xl">
        Up and running in 10 minutes
      </h1>
      <p class="mx-auto mt-6 max-w-2xl text-lg text-slate-600">
        Self-hosted on your own Linux box. The 30-day trial activates on first
        boot — no credit card, no sales call, no email confirmation step.
      </p>

      <figure class="mx-auto mt-12 max-w-4xl overflow-hidden rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white shadow-2xl ring-1 ring-slate-900/5">
        <img
          src="/images/feature-overview.png"
          alt="Perspectiv main dashboard showing the overview after first install — fleet health summary, recent alerts, and infrastructure tiles."
          class="block h-auto w-full"
          loading="lazy"
          decoding="async"
        />
        <figcaption class="border-t border-slate-200 bg-slate-50 px-4 py-2 text-xs text-slate-500">
          The overview dashboard — what you'll see after creating your first admin user.
        </figcaption>
      </figure>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-white py-12">
    <div class="container-prose space-y-10">
      <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight text-slate-900">
          Before you start
        </h2>
        <ul class="mt-3 space-y-2 text-base text-slate-600">
          <li>A Linux host with Docker + Docker Compose (Ubuntu 22.04+ or similar)</li>
          <li>Starter tier (up to 100 devices): 8 GB RAM, 250 GB SSD; scales per tier (<a href="/pricing" class="text-brand-700 underline">see pricing</a>)</li>
          <li>Network access from the host to whatever devices you want to monitor</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight text-slate-900">
          Install
        </h2>
        <p class="mt-3 text-base text-slate-600">
          Three commands and you're at the bootstrap admin page:
        </p>
        <pre class="mt-4"><code>{`git clone https://github.com/perspectiv-net/perspectiv.git
cd perspectiv
cp .env.example .env
$EDITOR .env       # set POSTGRES_PASSWORD, LETSENCRYPT_EMAIL, PERSPECTIV_HOSTNAME
docker compose up -d`}</code></pre>
        <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-slate-500">
          Watch the logs with <code>docker compose logs -f perspectiv</code>.
          When you see <code>[100%] Ready.</code> browse to your hostname,
          create your first admin user, and you're in.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="rounded-xl border border-brand-200 bg-brand-50 p-6">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-slate-900">
          Want the paste-friendly walkthrough?
        </h3>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-700">
          The full step-by-step quickstart includes the Ubuntu Docker
          install path, the workstation hosts-file step (so your browser
          can reach <code>perspectiv.local</code>), and lab-vs-production
          guidance for TLS.
        </p>
        <div class="mt-4">
          <a
            href="https://github.com/perspectiv-net/perspectiv/blob/main/docs/quickstart.md"
            class="btn-primary text-sm"
          >
            Open the full quickstart on GitHub
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight text-slate-900">
          What you get during the trial
        </h2>
        <ul class="mt-3 space-y-2 text-base text-slate-600">
          <li><span class="font-semibold text-slate-900">30 days</span> from first boot</li>
          <li><span class="font-semibold text-slate-900">10 fully-monitored devices</span> — SNMP, WMI, agent</li>
          <li><span class="font-semibold text-slate-900">Unlimited ICMP-only devices</span></li>
          <li><span class="font-semibold text-slate-900">Every feature unlocked</span> — no module gating</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-4 text-base text-slate-600">
          Need a longer evaluation or higher device count for a real pilot? See
          the <a href="/charter">Charter Program</a> — design partners get
          extended trials (typically 90 days, 250+ devices) plus complimentary
          professional services.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight text-slate-900">
          Migrating from another tool?
        </h2>
        <p class="mt-3 text-base text-slate-600">
          Charter customers migrating from SolarWinds, PRTG, Zabbix, or
          LibreNMS get free migration assistance from us — let us know your
          source platform when you reach out at{' '}
          <a href="mailto:sales@perspectiv.net">sales@perspectiv.net</a>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <CTA
    heading="Ready to give it a real test?"
    body="Spin up a VM, follow the quickstart, see how far you get in 10 minutes."
  />
</BaseLayout>
